# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# Build output (justfile's `build` recipe)
/bin/

# Generated from .templ sources by `templ generate` (justfile's `generate`
# recipe runs before build/run/test/lint, so these are never committed —
# the .templ file is the source of truth).
*_templ.go

# SQLite database files (Story #3's data layer)
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm

# Generated from internal/platform/db/query/*.sql by `sqlc generate`
# (justfile's `generate` recipe), same reasoning as *_templ.go above —
# the .sql query files and migrations are the source of truth.
/internal/platform/db/sqlc/

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# Claude Code: session/interaction memory, never committed (org convention,
# see attested-delivery/CLAUDE.md §10). Durable repo docs go in AGENTS.md.
CLAUDE.local.md
